text: The Kahlenberg Transmitter is a facility for FM- and TV on the Kahlenberg near Vienna. It was established in 1953 and used until 1956 an antenna on the observation tower Stefaniewarte. From 1956 to 1974 a 129-metre-high guyed mast built of lattice steel was used. Since 1974 a 165-metre-high guyed steel tube mast has been used, which is equipped with rooms of technical equipment. ==See also== List of masts ==References== ==External links== * *http://www.skyscraperpage.com/diagrams/?b10351 Category:Radio masts and towers in Europe Category:Towers in Austria Category:Broadcast transmitters Category:Observation towers Category:1953 establishments in Austria Category:Towers completed in 1953
